Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Shallot{1}.

Roast the potatoes: Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @Dried Thyme{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast ~{12-13%minutes}, toss, then continue roasting until golden brown, another ~{12-13%minutes}.

Cook the pork: Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{4%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Season @Boneless Pork Chops{12%ounce} on all sides with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add to pan and sear until golden brown and just barely cooked to desired doneness, ~{4-5%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside.

While pork cooks, toss @Broccoli Florets{8%ounce} in a #medium bowl{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Spread on other side of baking sheet with potatoes. Roast until slightly crispy, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Add shallots and a drizzle of oil to same pan you cooked pork in over medium heat. Toss until lightly caramelized, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add @Balsamic Vinegar{2%tablespoon} and simmer until syrupy and reduced by half. Swirl in @Cherry Jam{1%tablespoon} and @water{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper. Taste and add @?Sugar{1/2%teaspoon}, if preferred, to sweeten. Remove pan from heat and swirl in @Butter{1%tablespoon}.

When potatoes are almost done, add pork chops to pan with glaze over medium heat, and turn until thoroughly coated and heated through. Serve alongside broccoli and potatoes. Enjoy!